args: I'm in! Ha! Who would've thought sneaking\ninto the castle could be so easy? Me,\nthat's who! Because I am a GENIUS!
Say, you hear something just now?\nSounded like someone yelling about...\nbeing a genius?
Cripes! Keep your mouth shut, Emile,\nor this will all have been for nothing!
Footsteps from the other direction?\nBlast! I've nowhere to run!
What will I do, what will I do,\nwhat will I—HMPHGH?!
Okay, I SWEAR I heard something\nover there...
Looks like we managed to slip away.

Apologies, Your Majesty! Even if I was
trying to help, it was terribly inappropriate
of me to place my hand over your mouth
as I did!
*gaaaaasp* *wheeeeeeze* It's...it's fine.\nYou saved me, so I'll let it slide just\nthis once, er...Saboa, is it?
I am. And welcome home...My Emperor.\nWAAAAAAAAH!
Heavens above, man! Are you crying?
I'm just so relieved to find you alive,\nEmperor Emile!
Also, how dare you think me dead, fool!\nNo mere poison can lay ME low!
It gladdens me to see you as spirited\nas ever, Majesty.
But we cannot afford to revel in reunion\nnow. You've come to reclaim your rightful\nplace on the throne, have you not?
Of course! Why else would I be here?
Then we should go to the dungeon\nand set about freeing Magnus.
Why is Magnus in the dungeon?
He spoke out against the new emperor's\ntyranny and was imprisoned for it.

We always believed you would return to us
someday, Majesty. Now let us rendezvous
with Magnus and devise a plan to return
your throne to you!
Saaay, wait a minute. Ain't you...?
Sorry, but I've not the time nor inclination\nto bandy either words or fists with brutes.\n...GET HIM, SABOA!
That voice... But it cannot be!
Thank heavens you're okay, my friend!\nAs you can see, Emperor Emile has\nreturned to us.
Of course I did! This castle—nay, this\nCOUNTRY—belongs to me, and I would\nnever leave it behind!
But I need the assistance of you both if\nI am to transform this nation into one\nof peace.
Is that truly what you want?!
I'll thank you not to look quite so shocked.\nThis is something I must do for myself.
None of those miserable commoners out\nthere will ever understand my talent\nif they can't do more than just survive.
Therefore, I will turn ours into a peaceful\nnation so they finally give me the respect,\nlove, and worship I so richly deserve!
Now let's come up with a plan to\ntake back my empire!
Did you both forget how to speak\nin the time I was gone?
No, Majesty. I was just thinking how you\nreally haven't changed at all.
I couldn't agree more. But for now,\nlet's discuss our plan.

Ah, wonderful! You already have one!
...Yes. ...Yes, I see. That just might...
ARE YOU A PAIR OF DUNDERHEADS?!
That's the dumbest plan I've ever heard!
I am prepared for any punishment you\nwish to inflict on me afterward, Majesty.\nFor now, do you accept this plan?
It is the only way to get close to Werner—\nand as you've just arrived, there's no better\ntime to put it into action.
Oh, fine. Anything to get my empire back.

I've brought this scoundrel claiming to be
the old Emperor as per Emperor Werner's
orders. I request an audience with him as
soon as possible.
No, you brute. You wretch. You, uh...brute?\nI will have revenge yes I will ha ha ha.
I'd heard there was a suspicious person\nlurking about here. Excellent work.\nYou may enter.
(The fool fell for our trap hook, line,\nand sinker! Everything's going so well!)

(Saboa and Magnus are the ones who
have me right now, and they're going to
encourage Werner to confirm if I'm really
who I claim to be.)
(And once he leans in close, they'll both\ntake him out from behind!)
(Oh, you traitorous slime! I'm going to...\nWait, huh?)
N-no one's here! What's going on?
To think you'd throw your life away after\nyour miraculous survival. You're more\nof a fool than I ever thought.

Did you really think the three of you could
kill ME? Ha! ...And who's under that
helmet there? Magnus, maybe? Take it
off and show me who you are.
So you saw through our plan...
Why, I saw this coming from miles away!\nDid you never once consider how easy it\nwas for this idiot to enter the castle?

You couldn't sneak through a snowstorm
in a white suit! That said, I must admit to
finding myself admiring such unparalleled
faith in one's own pathetic skill.
Well, SOMEBODY has to say nice things\nabout me once in a while!
Well, I wouldn't worry about that anymore;\nI'm taking your head here and now.
I'll create an opening for you, Majesty!\nUse it to escape!
It's no use, Magnus. Look at all of my\nsoldiers. Even if you sacrifice yourself,\nhe'll be surrounded again in no time.

Besides, what good will it do to protect a
gutless coward like that? However...if you
willingly renounce your allegiance to him,
I will spare your lives.
(Crap, crap, crap! There's no way they\nwon't sell me out after a line like that!)
Emperor Emile is not the coward here,\nWerner—YOU are.
What did you say to me?

It is not cowardice to rely on others.
In fact, it is the mark of a wise ruler.
We are simply demonstrating that we
are worthy of such trust.
You only wormed your way into power\nthrough a yellow-bellied assassination\nattempt, so who's the real coward?
For your insolence, Magnus,\nyou will be the first to die.
Oooo, look at me! I'm a big bad emperor\nwho poisons people and fights them when\nI have them outnumbered! Ooo la la!
You know what I think? I think you're\ndoing this because you're SCARED of me!
Oh, don't like that? Then come face me\nlike a man! I'll wipe the floor with you\nand your whole chump Dyrenell family!
If you insist upon single combat,\nthen single combat you shall have.
You will serve as an example to all\nof what happens when I am defied.
Tomorrow, we will duel before the citizens\nof this country so the idiots you once ruled\ncan see you slaughtered in the street!
Why did you provoke him like that,\nYour Majesty?!
Are you serious? If you weren't around,\nI'd have one less person to protect me—\nand that's a problem.
I marvel at your willingness to sacrifice\nyourself for our sakes, Majesty...
Er, but...do you think you can win?
O-of course! I'm the great and powerful\nEmperor Emile!
(...Well, this is a fine mess. I'm in way\nover my head here, but I was so carried\naway I just up and said it!)
(How in Ilia's name am I going to\nget myself out of this mess?!)
